{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"alias":"educable-absurd-myna","creation_channel":"cli","description":"## Context\n\nSplit from S4 (rebar:6673-7636-a116-4f90). S4 landed the transport-seam half of routing core through the Backend port: the 4 transport-construction sites (applier/fetcher/run_differs/_attestation) now obtain their transport from select_backend(load_config()).transport, apply_inbound_records provider 'jira' literals flow from backend.vendor, apply_handlers imports AssigneeNotFoundError directly, and ~34 test doubles were migrated module-shaped -> transport-shaped. That change is behaviour-preserving (full reconcile suite green) and includes a neutrality gate for those sites.\n\n## Remaining work (deferred here)\n\nThe core *importer* sites still import the Jira mappers directly:\n- outbound_differ.py (_map_local_to_jira_fields), inbound_differ.py (_map_jira_to_local_fields), apply_inbound.py (_map_local_to_jira_fields)\n- outbound_comments.py + inbound_translate.py (lazy_load adf.py / comment_limits.py)\n- outbound_links.py holds _RELATION_TO_JIRA_LINK (Jira link-relation constant) in backend-neutral core\n\n## Why deferred / the constraint\n\nThese modules are loaded STANDALONE via importlib.util.spec_from_file_location in their unit tests (see tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/conftest.py). Routing them through select_backend() at module scope is fine (the registry import is light; adapters import is lazy inside select_backend), but their unit tests test the mapping logic in ISOLATION, so the differ functions must receive the mapper (backend.outbound/inbound/sanitizer) by DEPENDENCY INJECTION from their caller rather than importing it — a signature refactor across the differ/apply modules and their tests. This is substantial and reviewable on its own, so it was split from S4 rather than bundled.\n\n## Approach\n\nThread a Backend (or its outbound/inbound/sanitizer mapper) as a parameter into compute_outbound_mutations / the inbound differ / apply_inbound, obtained once by the core orchestrator (run_differs/reconcile, which may import select_backend) and passed down. Relocate _RELATION_TO_JIRA_LINK + ADF-sizing/value-maps into adapters/jira single-source. Keep behaviour identical (full reconcile suite is the oracle). Extend the neutrality gate to assert no differ/apply core module imports the vendor mappers.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n- [ ] outbound_differ/inbound_differ/apply_inbound/outbound_comments/inbound_translate no longer import outbound_fields/inbound_fields/adf/comment_limits directly; they receive the mapper via injection.\n- [ ] outbound_links._RELATION_TO_JIRA_LINK single-sourced under adapters/jira.\n- [ ] Full reconcile suite (unit+integration) green (behaviour-preserving); neutrality gate extended and green.\n- [ ] make lint && make typecheck && make test green.","id":"4af8-2d88-719e-4478","parent_id":"bbf1-82e1-cf9d-494a","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"task","title":"Route reconciler differ/apply core-importer sites off vendor mappers via dependency injection (S4 follow-up)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784759182972123001,"uuid":"362eadea-3730-4f62-8cb1-d31517c28ca2"}